    {
      "id": "radial-menu-grammar-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "First Ring Grammar",
      "position": {
        "x": 1220,
        "y": -520
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# First Ring Grammar\n\nThe first circle should be grouped into four stable sectors:\n\n- **Layout**: beautify, reroute, align, spacing\n- **Node Palette**: create, connect, palette entry\n- **Info**: inspect, reveal source, provenance\n- **Mode**: select, connect, edit, present\n\nThis keeps the radial menu compact enough for fast use while preserving a readable structure.",
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "radial-menu-decision-first-ring",
      "type": "decision",
      "label": "The first ring should group actions by function",
      "position": {
        "x": 1660,
        "y": -520
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "The first circle of the radial menu should be divided into Layout, Node Palette, Info, and Mode. Users should understand the menu by section before drilling into action specifics.",
        "rationale": "Functional grouping keeps the radial menu compact and scannable, and prevents it from becoming a flat wheel of unrelated icons.",
        "status": "decided",
